There are two things to Divine Science: detachment and Love. They can be applied independently, but must be applied together. Below, on an indentation level is a way in which what is written on a less indented level can be accomplished.

Practoce unselfed Love.
    Love.
        Be perfectly sincere.
            Strive to be perfectly sincere.
    Be detached from yourself.
        Renounce identification with form.
            Renounce the fruits of action. (detachment from the future)
                Devote your deeds to the Supreme, do all that you do as a selfless service to the Supreme.
            Renounce likes and dislikes. (detachment from the past and the present)
                Offer all that you experience as a selfless gift to the Supreme. Observe yourself objectively, as an impersonal witness.
